cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about a toolkit for neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also emphasizes the modular design of the toolkit, which suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and software engineering (SE), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the experiment configuration system, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a possible category. Finally, the use of neural networks in the toolkit suggests a connection to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
